8. The deeper philosophical question you hinted at

If the interface shifts from abstract computation to embodied simulation, the human mind becomes part of the system.

Instead of reading history, people could experience plausible worlds.

That could change how humans learn:

books → simulations → lived scenarios

Which loops back to your earlier insight:

fail small in training so you don’t fail in reality

Simulation becomes a civilization-scale training ground.

